INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(1,'2025-26',1,'GK','Initiate the short build-up (distribute to full-backs/CBs even under pressure — a fixed principle), command the box, cover the full penalty-area width behind a mid-block; sweeping is situational, not constant.','Measured (3 matches): centroid pinned to his own goal-line (x~10.1-10.5), laterally central (y~46-53); broad shallow coverage across the full box width; one match shows the furthest off-line range — sweeping only when the game demanded. High action volume (74+ in one match).','HIGH — deep base + full-width coverage + build-up involvement exactly match the brief; no evidence of over-aggressive sweeping that would break the mid-block.','gk_sweeper/Build-Up is right for the build-up brief; measured depth says the sweeping is situational, so Balanced focus is acceptable in match variants (used in the 로저스 CAM preset).','appearances player_id=1 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations build_up','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH (API-measured); note top-3 selection bias (best matches only).');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(2,'2025-26',2,'RB','Defend-first right-back: contain the opposing winger, hold the right touchline width, advance only one-at-a-time with the left FB (foundation rule), late box arrivals when Villa dominate.','Measured (3 matches): y~15-20 in every match — never drifts inside. Flank HEIGHT varies with the brief: one match defensive-leaning (def 38%/mid 42%), one balanced (def 29%/mid 41%), one camped high (mid 46%/att 32%).','HIGH — width discipline is absolute; height modulates per game plan exactly as the one-at-a-time rule predicts.','fb_fullback/Versatile (optimal) fits the height modulation; switch to Defend focus for containment briefs (e.g. vs Liverpool, 로저스 CAM preset).','appearances player_id=2 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations in_possession/modulation','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(3,'2025-26',3,'RCB','Right-side duel/aerial anchor, cover behind the advancing Cash, step out with the ball into right-centre midfield in possession, far-post set-piece threat.','Measured (3 matches): def|right 35-50% core, mid|centre 20-34% step-ins (largest vs Forest, x-centroid 33.6 in the highest-line match), att-third spikes only on set pieces (header goal vs Bologna away).','HIGH — textbook match between brief and footprint; the step-out carries are measured, not just narrated.','cb_defender/Balanced confirmed — measured midfield step-ins argue for Balanced over a pure-stopper Defend focus.','appearances 72-74 (measured); tactic_observations defence','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(4,'2025-26',4,'LCB','Left ball-playing CB: progress via carries and passes into the left half-space, feed Digne/Maatsen and the inverted left attack, step into midfield when Villa pin teams back; box arrivals on set pieces.','Measured (3 matches): y~67-71 left-centre constant. Depth scales with control: deep vs Bologna (70% own third), stepping into the middle third vs Fulham (54% mid) and Forest (x up to 97 — header + penalty won). Attacking-third volume near zero in open play.','HIGH — progression happens by stepping UP the left-centre channel, exactly the BPD brief; never wanders off the left channel.','cb_bpd/Build-Up confirmed unambiguously.','appearances player_id=4 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations build_up','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(5,'2025-26',5,'LB','Two-way left-back: hold the left touchline width for the inverted attack (Rogers cuts in, Digne provides width), advance one-at-a-time opposite Cash, deliver crosses/cutbacks; balance defensive recovery with attacking output.','Measured (3 matches): y~82-84 touchline-hugging in all three; average height climbs 45→51→53 with attacking-third share 21%→35%→41% depending on the brief; 52-86 touches, big two-way volume.','HIGH — constant width, modulated height; the cutback assist vs Liverpool (Rogers goal) is the duty executed at its peak.','fb_fullback/Versatile (optimal) fits; fb_wingback/Support for attacking variants — both already present in the DB/tool presets.','appearances player_id=5 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations in_possession','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(6,'2025-26',6,'LB','Attacking left-back variant (vs Digne''s balanced profile): high-and-wide starting position, runs through the left half-space to the byline, create overloads with the inverted left winger; still owns the full left-channel defensive lane.','Measured (3 matches): avg height 44-56/100 (well past a normal FB), y~81-83; end-to-end left channel coverage in every match — own box to opposition byline; goal vs Maccabi from a byline run; Brentford match: 115 heat points, 100 touches, 6 tackles.','HIGH — the most front-foot footprint of any defender measured, and the two-way volume shows the defensive lane isn''t abandoned.','fb_att_wb/Attack (bench mapping) confirmed; select him over Digne when the plan needs left-side overloads rather than crossing balance.','appearances player_id=6 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations modulation axis 4','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(7,'2025-26',12,'LDM','Pivot anchor: screen the back four, sit RIGHT-of-centre (Onana/Tielemans take the left lane), controlled circulation, cover for the advancing left side; occasional forward carries.','Measured: 26-match average-position sweep gives mean y=42.6 (12 right / 12 centre / 2 left) — a right-of-centre/central pivot; settled firmly right from October through the 11-win streak until his January injury. Depth: avg x mostly 39-54 — a halfway-line controller in dominant games (top-3 heatmaps show 47-66% middle-third share), deeper in contested ones.','HIGH on screening and circulation; PARTIAL on the old "deep-left anchor" framing — the LEFT half of that framing was a coordinate-inversion error (now corrected), and the DEEP half only holds in contested matches. (Top-3 dominance bias still applies to the depth question.)','RDM slot (corrected from LDM in the optimal XI). dm_holding/Ball-Winning still defensible as the foundation role, but measured depth in controlled games leans dm_dlp; collect 1-2 difficult-match heatmaps before switching.','appearances player_id=12 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations modulation','MEDIUM-HIGH — side question now settled by a 26-match API sweep; depth question still carries top-3 bias.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(8,'2025-26',16,'ST','Lone striker, three briefs in one: (1) occupy the central box for wide deliveries, (2) drop/link and lay off to the inside-cutting Rogers/McGinn, (3) run the channels in behind as the transition outlet (drift wide to open the box for the 10).','Measured (3 matches): all three briefs visible and cleanly separated by game type — Sunderland: near-pure central box occupation (2 headers from wide deliveries); Liverpool: central box + left-channel link play with Rogers; Man City (away, counter brief): deeper average, transition lanes halfway-to-box, central-right channel bursts.','HIGH — the footprint reshapes per game plan while the goal output stays constant (2 goals in each of the three matches); this is the system''s most brief-obedient attacker.','st_advanced/Versatile confirmed exactly — Versatile captures the box-occupier/link/channel-runner trinity better than Attack (pure poacher) would.','appearances player_id=16 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations in_possession','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted but the three matches happen to span three distinct game types (home rout, home clash, away counter), which mitigates it.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(9,'2025-26',13,'CAM','Central No.10: link pivot to attack, arrive late in the box, carry through the middle third; press alongside Watkins out of possession (4-4-2 block).','MOST-USED position: 21 starts, 1759 min, avg 7.10, best 8.5 (Leeds A) — his highest per-90 axis. Measured Liverpool 4-2 heatmap: roaming central creator, goal + assist.','HIGH — carries the largest minute load at the highest average output.','cam_playmaker/Roaming viable as a first-team alternative to Buendía at 10; keeps his LW slot open for Malen/Sancho rotations.','player_match_positions player_id=13; appearances Liverpool CAM (measured)','HIGH — full-season API position sweep.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(10,'2025-26',13,'LW','Inverted left forward: hold high-left, cut inside onto the right foot, shoot from range, combine with the overlapping Digne/Maatsen.','BEST-CEILING position: 13 starts, avg 6.91 but the two best games of his season (9.3 West Ham, 9.0 Sunderland H) and measured peaks (8.84/8.46 heatmaps) are all here. Boom-or-quiet profile: lower floor than CAM, higher ceiling.','HIGH in big games; average delivery is less consistent than at CAM.','w_insidefwd/Attack (current optimal) is correct for max ceiling; if consistency is preferred, play him CAM and field a natural LW.','player_match_positions player_id=13; appearances 8.84/8.46 LW heatmaps','HIGH — full-season API position sweep.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(11,'2025-26',13,'RM','Right-sided attacker (emergency/rotation): hold right width, cut in on the left channel.','WEAKEST axis: 8 starts, avg 6.33 — worst of any (player,position) pair in the squad sample. Measured best-RM heatmap (Man United A, 7.3) shows him constantly abandoning the flank to find central touches; the inverted-winger weapon does not transfer to the right.','LOW — the numbers and the movement pattern both say this deployment wastes him.','Do NOT map Rogers right in any game preset; if the right needs cover, McGinn or Guessand over Rogers.','player_match_positions player_id=13; appearances match_id=45 (measured)','HIGH — full-season API position sweep.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(12,'2025-26',14,'LW/left-10','Advanced left-of-centre creator: free movement between the left half-space and the centre, key passes, set-piece delivery; presses as the second striker in the 4-4-2 block.','MOST-USED position: 21 starts, 1541 min, avg 6.90 — AND his ceiling: 9.4 (Forest SF), 8.5 (Bournemouth), 8.3 (EL final) all measured LEFT-of-centre (centroids y64-72). The media "right-drift No.10" framing is dead: only 2 right-side starts all season.','HIGH in knockout/big matches; moderate consistency across the league season.','His optimal row is the No.10 (cam_playmaker/Roaming) — accurate IF the free role is understood as left-leaning; in a stricter setup use an AML/left-10 slot. Never map him right.','player_match_positions player_id=14; appearances 75-77 (measured)','HIGH — full-season API position sweep.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(13,'2025-26',14,'pivot-left','Deeper left No.8: two-way shuttling, ball circulation from the left half-space, late box arrivals.','RELIABILITY position: 8 starts, avg 7.09 — his highest per-start average, above the advanced role. Measured (Newcastle A, 7.9, goal): def|left 31% + mid|left 22% genuine defensive work (4 tackles) plus a box arrival.','HIGH — quietly his most consistent deployment.','In-game: a CM/left-8 with Balanced or Build-Up focus is a legitimate second mapping for rotation-heavy setups; keeps his creativity while adding defensive presence.','player_match_positions player_id=14; appearances match_id=18 (measured)','HIGH — full-season API position sweep.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(14,'2025-26',10,'RM','Right of the midfield four: hold width in the block, half-space runs in possession, press the opposing LB, arrive at the far post.','MOST-USED position: 21 starts, 1672 min, avg 7.08, best 8.7 (Forest SF) + 8.6/8.5 — his ceiling games are all here. Measured heatmaps: right half-space and channel, edge-of-box arrivals (goals).','HIGH — the captain''s defining role in the streak side.','wm_widemid/Support (current optimal) confirmed for the foundation XI.','player_match_positions player_id=10; appearances McGinn RM heatmaps','HIGH — full-season API position sweep.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(15,'2025-26',10,'pivot-right','Right of the double pivot (deeper No.8): two-way engine, carry out of pressure, support the RB, arrive late.','BEST-AVERAGE position: 7 starts, avg 7.30 — higher than his RM average, concentrated in hostile away games. Measured (Feyenoord A, 7.9, goal): full-length two-way coverage (x3-99), mid|centre+mid|right core with real recovery work.','HIGH — trades width for control and his ratings rise.','Legit second mapping: CM-right/dm-adjacent role with Balanced focus for away/守-variant presets instead of a natural DM.','player_match_positions player_id=10; appearances match_id=3 (measured)','HIGH — full-season API position sweep.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(16,'2025-26',10,'CAM','Central 10 (rotation): between-the-lines connector, second-striker press.','4 starts, avg 6.90. Measured (West Ham H, 7.8, goal): dead-central connector (mid|centre 35%), compact x29-87 — functional but his press/box-crash value is better spent wide-right or deep-right.','MEDIUM — serviceable, not additive.','Do not prefer; use only when both Buendía and Rogers are unavailable.','player_match_positions player_id=10; appearances match_id=22 (measured)','HIGH — full-season API position sweep.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(17,'2025-26',9,'pivot-left','Deep-lying playmaker on the left of the pivot: dictate tempo from deep, progressive passing, late box arrival (EL final goal).','MOST-USED and BEST position: 11 starts avg 7.32 (+10 centre starts avg 7.24 — same role straddling the lane boundary; combined 21 starts ~7.28), best 8.4 (EL final, goal). Measured heatmaps: deeper distributor left-of-centre.','HIGH — the streak side''s tempo source when Kamara was injured; season-best games came here.','dm_dlp/Build-Up (current bench mapping) confirmed — and he is the first-choice LDM partner for Kamara(RDM) in the corrected pivot geometry.','player_match_positions player_id=9; appearances Tielemans deep heatmaps','HIGH — full-season API position sweep.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(18,'2025-26',9,'CAM','Free 10 (left-leaning): deep-connecting metronome between the lines rather than a box creator.','7 starts, avg 7.24, best 8.4. Measured (Forest H, 7.9, assist): 123 touches in 90 min — nearly double a normal 10''s volume; left-leaning full-pitch distribution.','HIGH as a control-10; does not provide a classic creator''s box presence.','Viable control-variant 10 (cam_playmaker/Build-Up-ish) for matches where Villa expect to dominate possession; pivot remains his prime slot.','player_match_positions player_id=9; appearances match_id=41 (measured)','HIGH — full-season API position sweep.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(19,'2025-26',8,'pivot (all lanes)','Box-to-box side of the double pivot: screen, duel, surge into the box (headed goals); take whichever lane the partner does not.','SIDE-AGNOSTIC: 15 centre starts (avg 7.21, best 8.1), 8 right (7.04), 6 left (7.05) — near-identical output on all three lanes; left of Kamara in the streak, right of Tielemans after. Measured heatmaps on centre (Man City 8.1), left (Bournemouth 8.2) and right (Newcastle A 7.3) all show the same mid-block screening + box-surge pattern.','HIGH — the pivot''s universal adapter; his rating is partner-independent.','dm_boxcrasher/Balanced confirmed; slot him LDM or RDM freely per partner — corrected optimal XI has him LDM next to Kamara(RDM).','player_match_positions player_id=8; appearances Onana heatmaps x4 (measured)','HIGH — full-season API position sweep.');
